headlines.description: Different team, familiar result for Ryan Fitzpatrick against the Jacksonville Jaguars.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fitzpatrick handles Jaguars again, this time with Dolphins

headlines.description: Chicago's Nick Foles threw three touchdown passes in the fourth quarter to hand the Atlanta Falcons another humiliating defeat, rallying the Bears from a 16-point deficit for a 30-26 victory on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Another Falcons collapse: Foles' 3 TDs lead 30-26 Bears win

events.name: Los Angeles Rams at Buffalo Bills

headlines.description: Josh Allen completed a 3-yard touchdown pass to tight Tyler Kroft with 15 seconds remaining, and the Buffalo Bills survived to beat the Los Angeles Rams 35-32 after squandering a 25-point lead on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bills rally to beat Rams 35-32 after blowing 25-point lead

headlines.description: Baker Mayfield threw two touchdown passes, Nick Chubb ran for two more and the Cleveland Browns moved over .500 for the first time since 2014 with a 34-20 win Sunday over the Washington Football Team, which lost rookie defensive end Chase Young to a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Mayfield, Chubb lead Browns past Washington and over .500

headlines.description: Stephen Gostkowski made his career-high sixth field goal of game, a 55-yarder with 1:48 left that lifted undefeated Tennessee to a 31-30 victory over the Minnesota Vikings on Sunday after Derrick Henry and Ryan Tannehill carried the Titans on another...
headlines.shortLinkText: Titans top winless Vikes 31-30; Gostkowski has 6 FGs

events.name: Las Vegas Raiders at New England Patriots

headlines.description: Rex Burkhead scored three touchdowns and Bill Belichick became the third coach in NFL history to reach 275 regular-season victories in the New England Patriots' 36-20 win over the Las Vegas Raiders on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Burkhead's 3 TDs power Patriots to 36-20 win over Raiders

events.name: San Francisco 49ers at New York Giants

headlines.description: The San Francisco 49ers didn't need quarterback Jimmy Garopollo and a slew of missing starters on the dreaded MetLife Stadium turf.
headlines.shortLinkText: Banged up 49ers win again at MetLife, beat winless Giants

headlines.description: Joe Burrow kept his team from losing again. So did Carson Wentz after several mistakes.
James Conner ran for 109 yards and the go-ahead touchdown midway through the fourth quarter as the Pittsburgh Steelers stayed perfect by rallying past the Houston Texans 28-21 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Steelers stay perfect, keep Texans winless in 28-21 victory

events.name: New York Jets at Indianapolis Colts

headlines.description: Xavier Rhodes delivered the first punch for the Indianapolis Colts on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Colts defense, Rivers come up big as Colts ground Jets 36-7

events.name: Carolina Panthers at Los Angeles Chargers

headlines.description: Carolina's defense forced three Los Angeles turnovers, Joey Slye kicked five field goals and the Panthers beat the Chargers 21-16 on Sunday, giving coach Matt Rhule his first NFL victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Panthers beat Chargers 21-16 for Rhule's first NFL victory

events.name: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at Denver Broncos

headlines.description: Tom Brady threw three touchdown passes and  Shaq Barrett  celebrated his homecoming with a pair of sacks, one for a safety, in Tampa Bay's 28-10 victory over the winless Denver Broncos on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brady, Barrett lead Buccaneers past  Broncos 28-10

headlines.description: Matt Prater made a 39-yard field goal as time expired, Matthew Stafford threw two touchdown passes and the Detroit Lions snapped an 11-game losing streak dating to last season by beating the Arizona Cardinals 26-23 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lions snap 11-game losing streak, beat Cardinals 26-23

headlines.description: DK Metcalf made up for a huge first-half blunder by catching a 29-yard touchdown pass from Russell Wilson with 1:47 remaining, and the Seattle Seahawks held off the Dallas Cowboys 38-31 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wilson throws 5 more TDs, Seahawks topple Cowboys 38-31

events.name: Green Bay Packers at New Orleans Saints

headlines.description: Aaron Rodgers passed for 283 yards and three touchdowns, and the Green Bay Packers remained unbeaten with a 37-30 victory over the New Orleans Saints on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rodgers, Packers unbeaten with 37-30 victory over Saints

events.name: Kansas City Chiefs at Baltimore Ravens

headlines.description: Patrick Mahomes put on a scintillating show while outperforming Lamar Jackson, and the Kansas City Chiefs deftly played the role of defending Super Bowl champions in a 34-20 thumping of the Baltimore Ravens on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mahomes outplays Jackson to lead Chiefs past Ravens 34-20
